---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import HeroSection from '../components/HeroSection.astro';
import CTAButton from '../components/CTAButton.astro';
import FAQAccordion from '../components/FAQAccordion.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Prolotherapy Treatment"
  description="Prolotherapy is a regenerative injection therapy that uses concentrated dextrose to trigger natural tissue healing. Learn about prolotherapy for arthritis, tendon injuries and back pain with Dr. Colin MacLeod ND in Halifax."
  focusKeyword="prolotherapy Halifax"
>
  <HeroSection
    title="Prolotherapy"
    compact
    video={{ src: "https://www.youtube.com/embed/SBGjz31fZVI", title: "Prolotherapy Overview" }}
  >
    <p>Prolotherapy is a regenerative injection treatment that harnesses your body's natural healing ability to repair damaged joints, tendons and ligaments.</p>
    <CTAButton slot="cta" />
  </HeroSection>

  <!-- What is Prolotherapy Section -->
  <section class="py-16 lg:py-24 bg-white">
    <div class="section-shell">
      <div class="grid lg:grid-cols-2 gap-12 items-center">
        <div class="order-2 lg:order-1">
          <img
            src="/images/treatments/prolotherapy-knee-injection.png"
            alt="Dr. MacLeod performing prolotherapy injection on patient's knee"
            class="rounded-3xl shadow-xl w-full"
            width="800"
            height="800"
            loading="lazy"
          />
        </div>
        <div class="order-1 lg:order-2">
          <h2 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-serif font-bold text-emerald-950 mb-8">What is Prolotherapy?</h2>
          <div class="prose prose-lg prose-emerald max-w-none">
            <p>
              Prolotherapy, short for "proliferative therapy," is an injection treatment that stimulates the body's natural healing response. A solution of concentrated dextrose is injected into damaged or weakened connective tissue, triggering a controlled inflammatory response that initiates tissue repair and regeneration.
            </p>
            <p>
              This technique has been used since the 1930s, when George Hackett, MD, developed it as a treatment for ligament and joint pain. Over the decades, prolotherapy has been refined and studied extensively, with dozens of clinical trials demonstrating its effectiveness for various musculoskeletal conditions.
            </p>
            <p>
              Unlike cortisone injections, which suppress inflammation and can weaken tissue over time, prolotherapy works with your body's natural healing mechanisms to strengthen and repair damaged structures. This makes it particularly valuable for chronic conditions where the goal is lasting repair rather than temporary symptom relief.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- How It Works Section -->
  <section class="py-16 lg:py-24 bg-emerald-50">
    <div class="section-shell">
      <h2 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-serif font-bold text-emerald-950 mb-12 text-center">How Prolotherapy Works</h2>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-8">
        <!-- Step 1 -->
        <div class="bg-white rounded-2xl p-8 shadow-lg card-hover">
          <div class="w-12 h-12 bg-emerald-700 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center mb-6">
            <span class="text-white font-bold text-xl">1</span>
          </div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-serif font-semibold text-emerald-950 mb-4">Injection</h3>
          <p class="text-slate-600">
            A solution of concentrated dextrose (typically 12.5-25%) is injected directly into the damaged tissue; whether that's a joint capsule, tendon attachment or ligament.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Step 2 -->
        <div class="bg-white rounded-2xl p-8 shadow-lg card-hover">
          <div class="w-12 h-12 bg-emerald-700 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center mb-6">
            <span class="text-white font-bold text-xl">2</span>
          </div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-serif font-semibold text-emerald-950 mb-4">Healing Response</h3>
          <p class="text-slate-600">
            The hypertonic solution triggers a controlled inflammatory response that activates growth factors including platelet-derived growth factor (PDGF), transforming growth factor-beta (TGF-Î²) and fibroblast growth factor.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Step 3 -->
        <div class="bg-white rounded-2xl p-8 shadow-lg card-hover">
          <div class="w-12 h-12 bg-emerald-700 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center mb-6">
            <span class="text-white font-bold text-xl">3</span>
          </div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-serif font-semibold text-emerald-950 mb-4">Tissue Repair</h3>
          <p class="text-slate-600">
            Over the following weeks, fibroblasts lay down new collagen, strengthening the damaged tissue. Multiple treatments build upon each other, progressively improving tissue integrity.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

